- Install latest Npgsql.EntityFrameworkCore.PostgreSQL via NuGet: `dotnet add package Npgsql.EntityFrameworkCore.PostgreSQL`
- Update project file to include provider:
```xml
<ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="Npgsql.EntityFrameworkCore.PostgreSQL" Version="latest-version" />
</ItemGroup>
```
- Apply migrations using EF Core CLI:
```bash
dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate --context YourDbContextName
dotnet ef database update --context YourDbContextName
```
- Key config options in `appsettings.json`:
```json
{
  "ConnectionStrings": {
    "DefaultConnection": "Host=your_host;Database=your_database;Username=your_username;Password=your_password;"
  }
}
```
- Ensure DbContext is configured to use PostgreSQL:
```csharp
public class YourDbContext : DbContext
{
    public YourDbContext(DbContextOptions<YourDbContext> options) : base(options)
    {
    }

    // DbSet properties here...
}
```
- Run migrations to create database schema: `dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate --context YourDbContextName`
